message.content:
Rule Learning, Neural Networks. 

Rule Learning is present in the text as the algorithm presented in the paper is for inducing decision trees with multivariate tests at internal decision nodes. This is a classic example of rule learning, where the algorithm learns rules to make decisions. 

Neural Networks are present in the text as the algorithm constructs each test by training a linear machine. Linear machines are a type of neural network that can be used for classification tasks.
